            <summary>
              <p>Single parchment folio; Parchment; Shelfmark: AKM 480; Qurʾānic Text: ; Lines per page: 15; Dimensions: 149 x 209; Script style: kūfī (Type D I); Estimated date of production:  900-1000.  The website of the Aga Khan Museum has the followig information (consulted June 16th 2021): "Qur'an leaf, Accession Number: AKM 480; Place:Near East or Iran; Dimensions:14.9 x 20.9 cm;  Date: 900s; Materials and Technique:Opaque watercolour, gold, ink, vellum" </p>
              <p>For an updated catalogue entry of a sister fragment of this Qurʾān kept at Qatar National Library, see <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/34/vers/45?handschrift=1410">Marcus Fraser, "Doha, Qatar National Library: HC.MS.2017.0053"</ref>.</p>
